cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper is about neural architecture search (NAS) for image denoising, which is a task related to computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new method for NAS, which involves gradient-based search strategies and employs operations with adaptive receptive field to build a flexible hierarchical search space. This suggests that the paper may also belong to categories related to machine learning and artificial intelligence, such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of GPUs for computation, which suggests that it may also belong to categories related to hardware and architecture, such as cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
